
[1]epaulment

   EPAUL'MENT, n. In fortification, a side-work or work to cover sidewise,
   made of gabions, fascines or bags of earth. It sometimes denotes a
   semi-bastion and a square orillon, or mass of earth faced and lined
   with a wall, designed to cover the cannon of the casemate.
